# healthcheck.conf.template
#
# /healthcheck auto-detects project shape (source dirs, test/lint
# commands, contracts) — you should only need this file when
# auto-detection doesn't match your layout or you want to steer
# the command.
#
# To use: copy to .claude/healthcheck.conf at project root and edit.
# Shell-sourceable. Any variable left unset falls through to
# auto-detection.
#
#   cp .claude/framework/healthcheck.conf.template .claude/healthcheck.conf
#   $EDITOR .claude/healthcheck.conf

# --- Project layout overrides ----------------------------------------
# Leave unset to let /healthcheck auto-detect from CLAUDE.md Commands
# section and common layouts. Space-separated paths.

# HEALTHCHECK_SOURCE_DIRS="02_src/reqtool 02_src/cli"
# HEALTHCHECK_TEST_DIRS="03_tests"

# --- Command overrides -----------------------------------------------
# Commands the automated check phase runs. Leave unset to auto-detect
# from CLAUDE.md Commands section (patterns: npm test, pytest, go test,
# cargo test, dotnet test, npm run lint, ruff check, eslint, etc.).

# HEALTHCHECK_TEST_CMD="cd 01_Project && npm test"
# HEALTHCHECK_LINT_CMD="cd 01_Project && npm run lint"

# --- Framework change window -----------------------------------------
# How many commits back to scan for framework file changes (controls
# whether /healthcheck runs the deep framework audit in Part 1.3).
# Default 10.

# HEALTHCHECK_FW_WINDOW=10

# --- Targeted review focus -------------------------------------------
# Free-form text passed to the reviewer subagent in Part 2 to steer
# attention — use this for known-hot areas of the codebase.

# HEALTHCHECK_REVIEW_FOCUS="thread safety in stage_0_ingest.py; async correctness in llm/api.py"

# --- Cold-start reminder interval ------------------------------------
# After this many days since the last successful /healthcheck run,
# cold start prompts the user to run one. Default 14.

# HEALTHCHECK_REMIND_DAYS=14
